---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Document Redactor"
	description="Privacy-first PDF redaction with a worker-based in-browser pipeline for searchable and scanned documents."
>
	<main class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-6xl flex-col gap-10 px-6 py-10 text-stone-900">
		<section class="glass-panel rounded-[2.4rem] border border-white/70 px-8 py-10 shadow-[0_28px_80px_rgba(44,38,25,0.12)]">
			<div class="max-w-4xl space-y-6">
				<span class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-[#cb8b63]/50 bg-[#fff5eb] px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[#8e4a24]">
					Privacy-first browser redaction
				</span>
				<div class="space-y-4">
					<h1 class="max-w-3xl text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
						Review every redaction before the PDF leaves your browser.
					</h1>
					<p class="max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">
						Document Redactor keeps extraction, OCR, detection, and export local to the browser. Searchable PDFs stay on
						the native-text lane. Scanned PDFs switch to OCR. The review UI stays in control either way.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
					<a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}app`} class="rounded-full bg-[#111] px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white">
						Open the app
					</a>
					<span class="rounded-full bg-white/80 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-stone-700">PDF only • 25 MB max • 30 pages max</span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
			<article class="glass-panel rounded-[1.8rem] border border-white/70 p-6">
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Two-lane processing</h2>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-stone-700">
					Native PDF text is extracted with PyMuPDF for searchable pages. Sparse or image-heavy pages switch to OCR with
					the same review surface.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="glass-panel rounded-[1.8rem] border border-white/70 p-6">
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Worker-first runtime</h2>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-stone-700">
					Pyodide, PyMuPDF, previews, OCR, and export run away from the main thread so the interface remains responsive
					during long documents.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="glass-panel rounded-[1.8rem] border border-white/70 p-6">
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Review stays mandatory</h2>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-stone-700">
					Detections are assistive only. You approve, reject, or draw manual boxes before export. True PDF redaction is
					the default path, with flattened export only as an explicit fallback.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
